<i>Podocarpus dacrydioides</i>), and black pines (<i>Rimu</i> or <i>Dacrydium cupressinum</i>), which with their regualarly-formed tops generally towered high above the other forest foliage; although here and there black beeches (<i>Fagus fusca</i>), 100 feet high, and 7 to 8 feet in diameter, were also to be seen.
